description: From Middle English westi, westig (“desolate, deserted, lonely”), from Old English wēstiġ (“waste, deserted”), from wēste (“waste, desert”) + -iġ (“-y”). See waste.

adjectives.description: westy (comparative more westy, superlative most westy)

description: Origin obscure. Probably from Middle English westi (“desolate, deserted, lonely”) (see above), or possibly related to Scots weest (“depressed, uneasy, anxious”).

adjectives.description: westy (comparative more westy, superlative most westy)

examples: Whiles he lies wallowing, with a westy head
